   "source": [
    "## 6. Key Insights"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print(\"\"\"\n",
    "KEY FINDINGS:\n",
    "═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n",
    "\n",
    "🏆 BEST APPROACH: Rolling Window (4 weeks → 1 day)\n",
    "   • MAE: 2.3205 knots (9.3% better than traditional ARIMA)\n",
    "   • Forecast has actual variation (std dev: 2.8001)\n",
    "   • Captures daily wind speed changes\n",
    "\n",
    "WHY ROLLING WINDOWS WORK BETTER:\n",
    "\n",
    "1️⃣  AVOIDS SEASONAL CONFLICTS\n",
    "   • 2-year data: Summer (high wind) + Winter (variable) patterns clash\n",
    "   • 4-week data: Only captures TODAY'S weather regime\n",
    "   • ARIMA learns LOCAL patterns, not conflicting global trends\n",
    "\n",
    "2️⃣  BETTER STATIONARITY\n",
    "   • Longer data has seasonal trends (non-stationary)\n",
    "   • Recent 4 weeks are much more stable\n",
    "   • Less differencing needed = cleaner forecasts\n",
    "\n",
    "3️⃣  CAPTURES SHORT-TERM MEMORY\n",
    "   • Weather systems (high/low pressure) last 3-7 days\n",
    "   • Using 4 weeks keeps model in same weather regime\n",
    "   • Old winter data doesn't confuse current forecasts\n",
    "\n",
    "4️⃣  REAL-WORLD PRACTICE\n",
    "   • Wind farm operators use 2-4 week rolling windows\n",
    "   • Energy traders retrain daily with new data\n",
    "   • This is INDUSTRY STANDARD!\n",
    "\n",
    "RECOMMENDATION:\n",
    "═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n",
    "✅ Use 14-28 day rolling windows for wind/solar forecasting\n",
    "✅ Retrain model DAILY with new observations\n",
    "✅ Forecast 1-7 days ahead (rolling windows work for multiple horizons)\n",
    "✅ This is production-ready for renewable energy forecasting!\n",
    "\"\"\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 7. Creating a Function for Production Use"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def rolling_arima_forecast(data, window_size=28, forecast_horizon=1, order=(1, 1, 1)):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Rolling window ARIMA forecasting.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Parameters:\n",
    "    -----------\n",
    "    data : array-like\n",
    "        Time series data\n",
    "    window_size : int\n",
    "        Size of rolling window (default: 28 days)\n",
    "    forecast_horizon : int\n",
    "        How many steps ahead to forecast (default: 1)\n",
    "    order : tuple\n",
    "        ARIMA order (p, d, q) (default: (1, 1, 1))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "    --------\n",
    "    predictions : array\n",
    "        Forecasted values\n",
    "    actuals : array\n",
    "        Actual values from test set\n",
    "    errors : dict\n",
    "        Dictionary with MAE, RMSE, MAPE\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    predictions = []\n",
    "    actuals = []\n",
    "    \n",
    "    for i in range(len(data) - window_size - forecast_horizon):\n",
    "        try:\n",
    "            # Train on rolling window\n",
    "            window_data = data[i:i + window_size]\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Fit ARIMA\n",
    "            model = ARIMA(window_data, order=order)\n",
    "            fit = model.fit()\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Forecast\n",
    "            pred = np.array(fit.get_forecast(steps=forecast_horizon).predicted_mean)[-1]\n",
    "            actual = data[i + window_size + forecast_horizon - 1]\n",
    "            \n",
    "            predictions.append(pred)\n",
    "            actuals.append(actual)\n",
    "        except:\n",
    "            continue\n",
    "    \n",
    "    predictions = np.array(predictions)\n",
    "    actuals = np.array(actuals)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Calculate metrics\n",
    "    mae = mean_absolute_error(actuals, predictions)\n",
    "    rmse = np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(actuals, predictions))\n",
    "    mape = np.mean(np.abs((actuals - predictions) / actuals)) * 100\n",
    "    \n",
    "    errors = {'MAE': mae, 'RMSE': rmse, 'MAPE': mape}\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return predictions, actuals, errors\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"✓ Function defined. You can now use it as:\")\n",
    "print(\"  preds, actuals, errors = rolling_arima_forecast(data, window_size=28)\")\n",
    "print(f\"  print(errors)\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 8. Example: Using the Function"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Example: Forecast with 4-week window and 3-day horizon\n",
    "print(\"Testing the rolling_arima_forecast function...\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "preds_test, actuals_test, errors_test = rolling_arima_forecast(\n",
